13/07/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- An earthquake measuring 4.9 on the Richter scale rocked Slovenia and neighbouring Italy and Croatia on Monday (12 July). The epicentre of the quake was near Kobarid in western Slovenia, near the border with Italy. Damage was reported there, with power and telephone lines cut. No damage was reported in Croatia or Italy. The Croatian Seismological Institute put the earthquake at 5.4 on the Richter scale.
In other news, the first Croatian-Slovenian joint patrols began Monday at the Macelj border crossing, in a bid to curb trans-border crime. Establishment of the patrols was stipulated in a bilateral agreement on border security co-operation signed in 2002. (STA, HINA, HRT, Nova TV, AFP - 12/07/04)
